## Establishing Rules

Why make a class you can't build? Because it forces strict rules on any child class that `extends` it!

```dart
abstract class Shape {
  // An empty method with NO body {}
  void draw(); 
}
```
Because `draw()` has no body, any class (like `Square`) that `extends Shape` is FORCED by Dart to provide its own `@override void draw() {}` code. If it doesn't, the app crashes!

## Forcing the Issue

Abstract classes are like legal contracts.

```dart
abstract class Database {
  void saveData(); // Empty contract
}

// To be a valid database, LocalDB MUST write the saveData code.
class LocalDB extends Database {
  @override
  void saveData() {
    print('Saved to phone!');
  }
}
```
This guarantees your entire team writes predictable code.

